        public void open​(LaunchOptions launchOptions)
        Description copied from interface: AppLauncher

        Open a specific App configured in the passed LaunchOptions. Each App has it's own set of parameters. For this reason a set of more concrete LaunchOptions objects can be used.

        Specified by:

      • openUrl

        public void openUrl​(java.lang.String url)
        Description copied from interface: AppLauncher

        Opens an URL with the best possible App. E.g. it will open a mailto url with the email app.

        Specified by:
        openUrl in interface AppLauncher
        Parameters:
        url - The url to open. Needs to be a valid url and must not be null.
